# gt-restic password example
# Copy this to 'password' and replace with your restic password:
#   cp ~/.config/gt-restic/password.example ~/.config/gt-restic/password
#   chmod 600 ~/.config/gt-restic/password
#
# This is the password restic uses to encrypt your backup.
# Pick something strong and store it somewhere safe (e.g. a password manager).
# If you lose this password, your backup is unrecoverable.

MyStr0ngP@ssw0rd!
